## Why This Is Asked
Tests understanding of maintaining auxiliary structures to achieve O(1) operations and how to handle duplicates and edge cases.

## Key Concepts
- Two-stack technique
- Invariants: minStack.top always <= all elements on main below
- Duplicate handling
- Space vs. time trade-offs

## Code Example
```javascript
class MinStack {
  constructor() {
    this.stack = [];
    this.minStack = [];
  }
  push(x) {
    this.stack.push(x);
    const m = this.minStack.length ? Math.min(x, this.minStack[this.minStack.length - 1]) : x;
    this.minStack.push(m);
  }
  pop() {
    if (!this.stack.length) return;
    this.stack.pop();
    this.minStack.pop();
  }
  top() {
    return this.stack[this.stack.length - 1];
  }
  getMin() {
    return this.minStack[this.minStack.length - 1];
  }
}
```

