## Why This Is Asked

Tests ability to design a prefix-based weighted index with duplicates and per-prefix aggregates. Uses a trie with per-node weight distributions to support fast sum and kth-largest queries by prefix.

## Key Concepts

- Trie over strings and per-node multisets of weights
- Handling duplicates via multiset entries
- Order-statistics to extract kth-largest with duplicates
- Trade-offs: update cost proportional to word length, query cost to O(log M)

## Code Example

```javascript
class TrieNode { constructor(){ this.next=new Map(); this.weights=new Multiset(); } }
class WeightedTrie { constructor(){ this.root=new TrieNode(); }
  insertWord(word,w){ let node=this.root; for(const ch of word){ if(!node.next.has(ch)) node.next.set(ch, new TrieNode()); node=node.next.get(ch); node.weights.add(w); } }
  eraseWord(word,w){ let node=this.root; for(const ch of word){ if(!node.next.has(ch)) return; node=node.next.get(ch); node.weights.deleteOne(w); } }
  sumWeightsForPrefix(prefix){ let node=this.root; for(const ch of prefix){ if(!node.next.has(ch)) return 0; node=node.next.get(ch); } return node.weights.sum(); }
  kthLargestWeightForPrefix(prefix,k){ let node=this.root; for(const ch of prefix){ if(!node.next.has(ch)) return null; node=node.next.get(ch); } return node.weights.kthLargest(k); }
}
```

