## Why This Is Asked

Tests understanding of dynamic order-statistics with duplicates and memory efficiency without full value-domain indexing.

## Key Concepts

- Coordinate compression
- Fenwick Tree or Segment Tree for counts
- K-th element via prefix-sum search
- Handling duplicates through counts

## Code Example

```javascript
class Fenwick {
  constructor(n){ this.n=n; this.ft=Array(n+1).fill(0); }
  add(i,delta){ for(; i<=this.n; i+= i & -i) this.ft[i]+=delta; }
  sum(i){ let s=0; for(; i>0; i-= i & -i) s+= this.ft[i]; return s; }
  kth(k){ let idx=0; let bit=1; while(bit<<1 <= this.n) bit<<=1; for(let d=bit; d; d>>=1){ let next=idx+d; if(next<=this.n && this.ft[next] < k){ idx = next; k -= this.ft[next]; } } return idx+1; }
}
```

