## Why This Is Asked

Candidates must handle time-decayed scoring with dynamic insert/erase and frequent top-k queries over a moving window, a realistic pattern in recommender and CDN analytics at large scale.

## Key Concepts

- Time-decayed scoring and exponential decay
- Windowed top-k queries with lazy deletions
- Maintaining running sums in a sliding window
- Trade-offs: lazy vs eager pruning, memory vs accuracy

## Code Example

```javascript
class TimeDecayStore {
  constructor(lambda) { 
    this.lambda = lambda; 
    this.map = new Map(); 
    this.heap = new MaxHeap(); 
    this.currentT = 0; 
  }

  insert(id, score, t) {
    this.map.set(id, { score, t_last: t });
    this.heap.insert({ id, decayedScore: score, t });
  }

  update(id, score, t) {
    this.map.set(id, { score, t_last: t });
    this.heap.insert({ id, decayedScore: score, t });
  }

  erase(id) {
    this.map.delete(id);
  }

  topKInLastWindow(k, t, W) {
    this.currentT = t;
    this.pruneExpired(t - W);
    const results = [];
    const temp = [];

    while (results.length < k && !this.heap.isEmpty()) {
      const item = this.heap.extractMax();
      const current = this.map.get(item.id);

      if (current) {
        const decayed = current.score * Math.exp(-this.lambda * (t - current.t_last));
        if (current.t_last >= t - W) {
          results.push({ id: item.id, decayedScore: decayed });
          temp.push({ id: item.id, decayedScore: decayed, t: current.t_last });
        }
      }
    }

    temp.forEach(item => this.heap.insert(item));
    return results;
  }

  sumScoresInWindow(t, W) {
    let sum = 0;
    for (const [id, { score, t_last }] of this.map) {
      if (t_last >= t - W) {
        sum += score * Math.exp(-this.lambda * (t - t_last));
      }
    }
    return sum;
  }

  pruneExpired(windowStart) {
    // Lazy pruning during queries
  }
}
```

